article.linkText: Beaubrun's 16 lead SFA over Seattle U 89-84 in OT
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- — Jalil Beaubrun had 16 points and 10 rebounds and AJ Cajuste hit a go-ahead jumper with 38 seconds left in overtime to rally Stephen F. Austin to an 89-84 victory over Seattle University on Thursday night. Nana Antwi-Boasiako added 16 points, eight rebounds and three steals for the Lumberjacks (12-6, 5-2 Western Athletic Conference). Kyle Hayman had 14 points and finished 6 of 11 from the field. Cajuste had 13 points. The Redhawks (10-8, 3-4) were led in scoring by Alex Schumacher, who finished with 24 points and seven assists. Brandton Chatfield added 16 points and 12 rebounds for Seattle U. In addition, John Christofilis had 16 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
